\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 35. D. fladnizensis} Wulfen in Jacq., {\i Mise. Austr. Bot.}{\b  1}: 147 (1779) ({\i D. wahlenbergii} Hartman). Flowering stem up to 8 cm, usually subglabrous. Cauline leaves usually 1(2); basal leaves linear-spathulate, obtuse, ciliate, otherwise glabrous, or variably covered with usually simple hairs. Inflorescence 2- to 12-flowered. Petals 2-3·5 mm, white. Silicula 2·5-7·5 mm, lanceolate-elliptical, glabrous; style c. 0·2 mm. 2n = 16. {\i Arctic Europe and mountains of Scandinavia and S. & C. Europe,from the Pyrenees to the E. Carpathians.} Au Cz Fe Ga Ge He Is It No Rm Rs(N, C) Sb Su.
