\pard\f0\fs28 Very variable and divided by some authors into several species. In northern Europe, the North American species{\b  D. lactea} Adams{\i  Mém. Soc. Nat. Moscou}{\b  5}: 104 (1817), is recognized as distinct on the basis of having basal leaves with some branched hairs and usually no cauline leaves, petals 3-5 mm, and style up to 0·5 mm. In the Alps, however, this distinction does not seem to be practicable.
